From 9b2712f777fd5688d8ed91b8c98c8018c8fb6fe5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Marco Giunta <marco_giunta@outlook.it>
Date: Sat, 25 Apr 2026 12:00:54 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 6/7] ALSA: hda/scodec: add AW88399 HDA side codec driver

Add an HDA side codec driver for the AWINIC AW88399 smart amplifier,
enabling its use as a companion amplifier on HDA systems where the
chip is connected via I2C to the host and driven alongside a primary
HDA codec (such as Realtek ALC287).

The driver is structured after the CS35L41 HDA side codec driver:

- aw88399_hda_i2c.c: I2C bus driver matching ACPI HID AWDZ8399 and
  serial-multi-instantiate device name "aw88399-hda".

- aw88399_hda.c: Core driver implementing HDA component binding,
  playback hooks (using the shared library's start/stop functions),
  ACPI subsystem ID retrieval, device index resolution from ACPI _UID
  or I2C address, and runtime/system power management.

- aw88399_hda_property.c: Property driver providing per-model quirk
  infrastructure. Uses ACPI subsystem ID matching to walk a table of
  model-specific fixup functions, following the pattern of
  cs35l41_hda_property.c. The quirk table is empty in this patch;
  device-specific entries are added in the next patch along with the
  corresponding Realtek fixups that activate the driver.

The driver depends on SND_SOC_AW88399_LIB for chip initialization,
firmware loading, and playback control, avoiding any dependency on
the full ASoC codec module.

Co-developed-by: Yakov Till <yakov.till@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Yakov Till <yakov.till@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Marco Giunta <marco_giunta@outlook.it>
